  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to persist chat position after scrolling around and clicking around.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: issue exist in mobile in https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4797,  https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/5185.\r\n(1) For desktop from my POV (the same behaviour in Telegram) position in chat history shouldn't change after:\r\n- switching between chats\r\n- open user profile from public chat and go back\r\n- go to profile and back\r\n- click on + and go back\r\n- in 1-1 chat click on `View profile` and go back\r\n\r\n(2) The user should be scrolled to last message after:\r\n- send a message\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nin (1) cases - chat postion is not changed\r\nin (2) cases - scroll to latest message\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nin (1) cases - scroll to latest message\r\nin (2) cases - chat postion is not changed\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open any 1-1 or public chat\r\n- Scrolling up to see history several days ago\r\n- Repeat (1) and (2) from summary\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: nightly 14/09/2018\r\n* Operating System: Mac OSx\r\n",
